title: Rust on wasm compiled with `trunk` crashes: 'rustc' panicked at 'failed to lookup `SourceFile` in new context', compiler/rustc_query_impl/src/on_disk_cache.rs:500:22

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
<!--
Thank you for finding an Internal Compiler Error! 🧊  If possible, try to provide
a minimal verifiable example. You can read "Rust Bug Minimization Patterns" for
how to create smaller examples.

http://blog.pnkfx.org/blog/2019/11/18/rust-bug-minimization-patterns/

-->

### Background
This bug does not trigger on the first invocation of `trunk serve`. From this behavior and the filename of the panicking code I am guessing it is scary caching code that is up to no good.

The first time through everything works as expected but things blow up when it is re-run. Wasm itself throws an runtime exception, which is what I was initially attempting to debug. Unrelated but if anyone knows how to fix that application logic error let me know.

#### Repro Steps
All steps are relative to where Cargo.toml is located and assume this is in the base directory.

1. `cargo clean; trunk clean; cargo build; trunk build`
2. `touch src/lib.rs`
3. `trunk serve`

### Code
#### Cargo.toml
```toml
[package]
name = "repro"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[lib]
crate-type = ["cdylib"]

[dependencies]
wasm-bindgen = "0.2"

[dependencies.web-sys]
version = "0.3.55"
features = [ "CanvasRenderingContext2d"
           , "Document"
           , "Element"
           , "HtmlCanvasElement"
           , "Window"
           ]
```

#### index.html
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>repro</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <canvas id="canvas_element"></canvas>
  </body>
</html>
```


#### index.js
```js
function external_fn() {
}
```

#### src/lib.rs
```Rust
use wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;
use wasm_bindgen::JsCast;

#[wasm_bindgen(module = "/index.js")]
extern "C" {
    fn external_fn();
}

#[wasm_bindgen(start)]
pub fn js_main() -> Result<(), JsValue> {
    external_fn();

    let document = web_sys::window()
        .ok_or(JsValue::from_str("no global window exists"))?
        .document()
        .ok_or(JsValue::from_str("should have a document on window"))?;
    let canvas = document.get_element_by_id("canvas_element")
        .ok_or(JsValue::from_str("unable to locate canvas_element canvas in document"))?
        .dyn_into::<web_sys::HtmlCanvasElement>()?;

    let _context = canvas
        .get_context("2d")?;

    Ok(())
}
```

If you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the
